Eclectic implings are implings that can be caught in the Impetuous Impulses minigame, and are located throughout Puro-Puro and Gielinor. The player needs at least 50 Hunter to capture this type of impling with a butterfly net or magic butterfly net, or at least 60 Hunter to capture it barehanded. Capturing an eclectic impling grants 30 Hunter experience (if caught on Puro-Puro) or 32 Hunter experience (if caught elsewhere in Gielinor). They are popularly hunted by players due to their 1/25 chance of giving a medium clue scroll when looted.

When captured, the player can loot the eclectic impling jar, leaving an item behind, or can trade it with Elnock Inquisitor. The player can trade one eclectic impling for 3 impling jars, or can trade 3 essence implings, 2 eclectic impings and one nature impling for a jar generator.

Often, people will "camp" an eclectic impling spawn point in Puro-Puro, looting and keeping the stackable drops, until they get a clue scroll. One of the best respawn points is the north-west corner of Puro-Puro, as there is a better chance for the impling to be trapped against the wall so it can't run away.

Loot[edit | edit source]

At current Grand Exchange prices, opening an eclectic impling jar gives 1,563 worth of loot, on average. This means opening eclectic impling jars marks an average profit of −4,125 per jar, however this does not include loot from clue scrolls.

On average, one would profit −103,114 to get a medium clue scroll from eclectic impling jars at current Grand Exchange prices, excluding the rewards from the completed Treasure Trails.
